import numpy as np
from scipy.stats import skewnorm, lognorm

# Define custom distributions for each feature based on provided statistics
target_thickness = skewnorm(0) # Approximately normal distribution with mean 1.02 and variance 16.9
pulse_width = lognorm() # Log-normal distribution to match high variance (mean=291, variance=1e6)
energy = lognorm() # Log-normal distribution for energy (mean=13.9, variance=2350)
spot_size = skewnorm(a=-8) # Skewed normal distribution with a mean around 3.6 and low variance
intensity = lognorm() # Log-normal distribution to match high variance (mean ~ 5e20, var ~ 4e41)
power = lognorm() # Log-normal distribution for power (mean~6e13, var~4e27)
cutoff_energy = skewnorm(a=-8) # Skewed normal distribution with a mean around 8.6 and low variance

# Generate random samples using custom distributions
target_thickness_samples = target_thickness.rvs(size=25)*10 + 0.5 # Adding an offset of 0.5 to match the statistics provided
pulse_width_samples = pulse_width.rvs(size=25) * np.sqrt(1e6/np.var(target_thickness_samples)) + 30 - np.mean(target_thickness_samples)*np.sqrt(1e6/np.var(target_thickness_samples)) # Scaling to match variance and adding an offset
energy_samples = energy.rvs(size=25) * np.sqrt(2350/np.var(pulse_width_samples)) + 14 - np.mean(pulse_width_samples)*np.sqrt(2350/np.var(pulse_width_samples)) # Scaling to match variance and adding an offset
spot_size_samples = spot_size.rvs(size=25) * 0.1 + 3.3 # Adding an offset of 3.3 to match the statistics provided
intensity_samples = intensity.rvs(size=25) * np.sqrt(4e41/np.var(spot_size_samples)) + 5.1 - np.mean(spot_size_samples)*np.sqrt(4e41/np.var(spot_size_samples)) # Scaling to match variance and adding an offset
power_samples = power.rvs(size=25) * np.sqrt(4e27/np.var(intensity_samples)) + 6.3 - np.mean(intensity_samples)*np.sqrt(4e27/np.var(intensity_samples)) # Scaling to match variance and adding an offset
cutoff_energy_samples = cutoff_energy.rvs(size=25) * 10 + 8.6 # Adding an offset of 8.6 to match the statistics provided

# Generate target material samples
target_material_samples = np.random.choice(['plastic', 'aluiminium', 'polypropylene', 'gold'], size=25)

# Combine all generated data into a single array
generated_data = [['plastic'] + list(np.round([t, pw, e, s, i, po, ce], 3)) for t, pw, e, s, i, po, ce in zip(target_thickness_samples, pulse_width_samples, energy_samples, spot_size_samples, intensity_samples, power_samples, cutoff_energy_samples)]
generated_data = np.array(generated_data)
print(generated_data)
```
